article.headline: Howard rallies past Hampton 30-29
article.story: WASHINGTON -- John Fleck kicked a 17-yard field goal with 21 seconds left to lift Howard to a 30-29 victory over Hampton on Saturday, capping a 23-point comeback. Howard (5-7, 3-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic) was down 26-7 midway through the third after Hampton's Christopher Dukes scored his second touchdown from 2 yards out. The Pirates (3-9, 2-6) appeared to be riding the momentum that led them to a 40-35 upset of nationally ranked Bethune-Cookman the previous week. But the Bison began a stampede to the end zone, scoring three straight TDs -- Greg McGhee scoring from the 24, and Aquaniu Freeman on runs from the 2 and the 6, grabbing a 27-26 lead with 7:04 to play. Hampton rallied for the lead one last time when Anthony Prevost kicked a 25-yard field goal with 3:38 to play. Howard's final drive covered 71 yards in a grinding 13 plays before Fleck hit the winner.
